Variable Definitions:
    let <ident> = <expr>

Blocks
    { <expr> ... }

Functions:
    fn (<type> <ident>, ...) <type> 

Stack Frame                         Location of first byte
    values in this scope            :: ...
    actual paramaters               :: SP + 0 ..
    return address                  :: SP - 8
    pointer to top of last frame    :: SP - 16
    scope depth                     :: SP - 24
    saved machine state             :: 
        R1                          :: SP - 32
        R2                          :: SP - 40
        R3                          :: SP - 48
        R4                          :: SP - 56
    value of R1 when looping back   :: SP - 64
    value of R2 when looping back   :: SP - 72
    return values                   :: ...

Instructions to:
    access value in this scope  :: LOAD (SP + <offset on stack>)
    access value in prior scope :: LOAD <R1> into (SP - 64)
                                   LOAD <R2> into (SP - 72)
                                   LOAD <depth var found> into <R1>
                                   LOAD ((SP-16) - 24) into R2
                                   IFEQ <R1> <R2> : Pull val from this frame
                                   ELSE continue
    Push Frame :: Calculate size of stored vals as TV (Top of values)
               :: Save register values into TV + 8 + 8 + size of returns
               :: push next scope depth 
               :: push current SP
               :: push return code address
               :: push paramaters
               :: pass control to new code

    POP Frame  :: Push return values to reserved space in SP - 80...
               :: Change SP to (SP - 16)
               :: Return control to return address

                                   